#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:28
msgid ""
"In most cases recovering a file is quite simple, assuming you know which "
"file you were editing (and the harddisk is still working).  Start Vim on the "
"file, with the \"-r\" argument added: >"
msgstr ""
"En la mayoría de los casos, recuperar un archivo es bastante sencillo, si "
"suponemos que sabe qué archivo estaba editando (y el disco duro aún "
"funciona). Inicie Vim con el archivo y el argumento «-r»: >"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "\tvim -r help.txt\n"
msgstr "\tvim -r ayuda.txt\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:34
msgid ""
"Vim will read the swap file (used to store text you were editing) and may "
"read bits and pieces of the original file.  If Vim recovered your changes "
"you will see these messages (with different file names, of course):"
msgstr ""
"Vim leerá el archivo de intercambio (empleado para almacenar el texto "
"editado) y puede que lea bits y porciones del texto original. Verá los "
"siguientes mensajes si todo ha ido bien (con nombres de fichero diferentes, "
"por supuesto)."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:41
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tUsing swap file \".help.txt.swp\" ~\n"
"\tOriginal file \"~/vim/runtime/doc/help.txt\" ~\n"
"\tRecovery completed. You should check if everything is OK. ~\n"
"\t(You might want to write out this file under another name ~\n"
"\tand run diff with the original file to check for changes) ~\n"
"\tYou may want to delete the .swp file now. ~\n"
msgstr ""
"\tUsing swap file \".help.txt.swp\" ~\n"
"\tOriginal file \"~/vim/runtime/doc/help.txt\" ~\n"
"\tRecovery completed. You should check if everything is OK. ~\n"
"\t(You might want to write out this file under another name ~\n"
"\tand run diff with the original file to check for changes) ~\n"
"\tYou may want to delete the .swp file now. ~\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "\t:write help.txt.recovered\n"
msgstr "\t:write ayuda.txt.recuperado\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:48
msgid ""
"Compare the file with the original file to check if you ended up with what "
"you expected.  Vimdiff is very useful for this |08.7|.  For example: >"
msgstr ""
"Compare el archivo con el original para ver si obtuvo lo que esperaba. "
"Vimdiff es muy útil para esta tarea |08.7|. Por ejemplo: >"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t:write help.txt.recovered\n"
"\t:edit #\n"
"\t:diffsp help.txt\n"
msgstr ""
"\t:write help.txt.recovered\n"
"\t:edit #\n"
"\t:diffsp help.txt\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:58
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Watch out for the original file to contain a more recent version (you saved\n"
"the file just before the computer crashed).  And check that no lines are\n"
"missing (something went wrong that Vim could not recover).\n"
"   If Vim produces warning messages when recovering, read them carefully.\n"
"This is rare though.\n"
msgstr ""
"Compruebe que el archivo original no contenga una versión más reciente\n"
"(guardó el archivo justo antes de que el sistema diese un fallo).\n"
"Compruebe también que no se ha omitido ninguna línea (algo ha ido mal\n"
"y Vim no pudo recuperar).\n"
"   Si Vim genera mensajes de advertencia al recuperar un archivo, lea\n"
"éstos cuidadosamente. Aún así, es poco habitual.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:66
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tUsing swap file \".help.txt.swp\" ~\n"
"\tOriginal file \"~/vim/runtime/doc/help.txt\" ~\n"
"\tRecovery completed. Buffer contents equals file contents. ~\n"
"\tYou may want to delete the .swp file now. ~\n"
msgstr ""
"\tUsing swap file \".help.txt.swp\" ~\n"
"\tOriginal file \"~/vim/runtime/doc/help.txt\" ~\n"
"\tRecovery completed. Buffer contents equals file contents. ~\n"
"\tYou may want to delete the .swp file now. ~\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:69
msgid ""
"This usually happens if you already recovered your changes, or you wrote the "
"file after making changes.  It is safe to delete the swap file now."
msgstr ""
"Habitualmente, esto ocurre si ya ha recuperado los cambios, o si editó el "
"archivo después de realizar cambios. En este momento ya puede eliminar el "
"archivo de intercambio."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:75
msgid ""
"It is normal that the last few changes can not be recovered.  Vim flushes "
"the changes to disk when you don't type for about four seconds, or after "
"typing about two hundred characters.  This is set with the 'updatetime' and "
"'updatecount' options.  Thus when Vim didn't get a chance to save itself "
"when the system went down, the changes after the last flush will be lost."
msgstr ""
"Es normal que los últimos cambios no se puedan recuperar. Vim vuelca los "
"cambios al disco duro cuando no teclea durante cuatro segundos, o tras "
"escribir unos doscientos caracteres. Esto se puede modificar con las "
"opciones 'updatetime' y 'updatecount'. De esta forma, cuando Vim no tiene "
"posibilidad de guardar cuando el sistema cae, tendrá los cambios del último "
"volcado."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "\tvim -r \"\"\n"
msgstr "\tvim -r \"\"\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "*11.2*\tWhere is the swap file?\n"
msgstr "*11.2* \t¿Dónde está el archivo de intercambio?\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:88
msgid ""
"Vim can store the swap file in several places.  Normally it is in the same "
"directory as the original file.  To find it, change to the directory of the "
"file, and use: >"
msgstr ""
"Vim puede guardar el archivo de intercambio en distintos lugares.  "
"Normalmente se encuentra en el mismo directorio que el archivo original.  "
"Para encontrarlo, cambie al directorio del archivo y escriba: >"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:90
#, no-wrap
msgid "\tvim -r\n"
msgstr "\tvim -r\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:96
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Vim will list the swap files that it can find.  It will also look in other\n"
"directories where the swap file for files in the current directory may be\n"
"located.  It will not find swap files in any other directories though, it\n"
"doesn't search the directory tree.\n"
"   The output could look like this:\n"
msgstr ""
"Vim usará una lista de archivos de intercambio que ha encontrado. También\n"
"buscará en otros directorios donde los archivos de intercambio para archivos\n"
"en el actual puedan encontrarse. No buscará archivos de intercambio en\n"
"otros directorios, ni siquiera en los subdirectorios.\n"
"   La salida se parecerá a esto:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_11.txt:111
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tSwap files found: ~\n"
"\t   In current directory: ~\n"
"\t1.    .main.c.swp ~\n"
