#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:105
#, no-wrap
msgid ":new"
msgstr ":new"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:111
#, no-wrap
msgid "*08.3*\tWindow size"
msgstr "*08.3*\tTamaño de ventana"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:115
msgid "The \":split\" command can take a number argument."
msgstr "La orden «:split» puede recibir un argumento numérico."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:115
msgid "If specified, this will be the height of the new window."
msgstr "Si se especifica, este será la altura de la nueva ventana."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:115
msgid ""
"For example, the following opens a new window three lines high and starts "
"editing the file alpha.c: >"
msgstr ""
"Por ejemplo, el siguiente abre una nueva ventana con una altura de tres "
"líneas y edita el archivo alpha.c: >"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:117
#, no-wrap
msgid ":3split alpha.c"
msgstr ":3split alpha.c"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:121
msgid "For existing windows you can change the size in several ways."
msgstr "Para ventanas ya existentes puede cambiar el tamaño de varias formas."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:121
msgid ""
"When you have a working mouse, it is easy: Move the mouse pointer to the "
"status line that separates two windows, and drag it up or down."
msgstr ""
"Cuando tiene un ratón, es fácil: Coloque el puntero en la línea de estado "
"que separa las dos ventanas y arrástrela."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "CTRL-W +"
msgstr "CTRL-W +"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:129
#, no-wrap
msgid "CTRL-W -"
msgstr "CTRL-W -"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:132
msgid ""
"Both of these commands take a count and increase or decrease the window size "
"by that many lines."
msgstr ""
"Ambas órdenes reciben un multiplicador que modificará la altura de ventana "
"ese número de líneas."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:132
msgid "Thus \"4 CTRL-W +\" make the window four lines higher."
msgstr "«4 CTRL-W +» hará la ventana cuatro líneas más alta."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:136
#, no-wrap
msgid "{height}CTRL-W _"
msgstr "{altura}CTRL-W _"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:141
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"That's: a number {height}, CTRL-W and then an underscore (the - key with Shift\n"
"on English-US keyboards)."
msgstr ""
"O sea: un número {altura}, CTRL-W y luego un guión bajo (Mayúsculas más la\n"
"tecla -)."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:141
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To make a window as high as it can be, use the CTRL-W _ command without a\n"
"count."
msgstr ""
"Para maximizar una ventana, use la orden CTRL-W _ sin ningún\n"
"multiplicador ni argumento."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:150
msgid "In Vim you can do many things very quickly from the keyboard."
msgstr "En Vim puede hacer muchas cosas muy rápidamente desde el teclado."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:150
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, the window resizing commands require quite a bit of typing."
msgstr ""
"Por desgracia, las órdenes de ajuste de las ventanas requieren mucho trabajo."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:150
msgid "In this case, using the mouse is faster."
msgstr "En este caso, usar el ratón es más rápido."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:150
msgid "Position the mouse pointer on a status line."
msgstr "Coloque el ratón sobre la línea de estado."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:150
msgid "Now press the left mouse button and drag."
msgstr "Ahora presione el botón izquierdo y arrastre."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:150
msgid ""
"The status line will move, thus making the window on one side higher and the "
"other smaller."
msgstr "La línea de estado se desplazará, ajustando el tamaño de la ventana."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:160
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The 'winheight' option can be set to a minimal desired height of a window and\n"
"'winminheight' to a hard minimum height."
msgstr ""
"La opción 'winheight' se puede ajustar a una altura mínima de ventana y\n"
"'winminheight' a un mínimo estricto."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:160
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Likewise, there is 'winwidth' for the minimal desired width and\n"
"'winminwidth' for the hard minimum width."
msgstr ""
"Del mismo modo, hay un ancho 'winwidth' para el ancho mínimo deseado y un\n"
"'winminheight' para un ancho mínimo estricto."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:160
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The 'equalalways' option, when set, makes Vim equalize the windows sizes\n"
"when a window is closed or opened."
msgstr ""
"La opción 'equalalways', cuando está activa, hace que Vim equilibre el\n"
"tamaño de las ventanas cuando éstas se cierran o se abren nuevas."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:163
#, no-wrap
msgid "*08.4*\tVertical splits"
msgstr "*08.4*\tDivisiones verticales"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:166
msgid "The \":split\" command creates the new window above the current one."
msgstr "La orden «:split» crea una nueva ventana sobre la actual."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:166
msgid "To make the window appear at the left side, use: >"
msgstr "Para hacer que una ventana aparezca en el lateral izquierda, use: >"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:168
#, no-wrap
msgid ":vsplit"
msgstr ":vsplit"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:171
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"or: >\n"
"\t:vsplit two.c"
msgstr ""
"o: >\n"
"\t:vsplit two.c"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:182
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"+--------------------------------------+\n"
"\t|/* file two.c */   |/* file one.c */  |\n"
"\t|~\t\t    |~\t\t       |\n"
"\t|~\t\t    |~\t\t       |\n"
"\t|~\t\t    |~\t\t       |\n"
"\t|two.c===============one.c=============|\n"
"\t|\t\t\t\t       |\n"
"\t+--------------------------------------+"
msgstr ""
"+--------------------------------------+\n"
"\t|/*archivo dos.c */ |/*archivo uno.c */|\n"
"\t|~                  |~                 |\n"
"\t|~                  |~                 |\n"
"\t|~                  |~                 |\n"
"\t|two.c===============one.c=============|\n"
"\t|                                      |\n"
"\t+--------------------------------------+"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:188
msgid ""
"There is also the \":vnew\" command, to open a vertically split window on a "
"new, empty file."
msgstr ""
"También hay una orden «:vnew», para abrir una partición vertical con un "
"archivo nuevo."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:190
#, no-wrap
msgid ":vertical new"
msgstr ":vertical new"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:195
msgid ""
"The \":vertical\" command can be inserted before another command that splits "
"a window."
msgstr ""
"La orden «:vertical» se puede insertar justo antes de otra orden que divida "
"la ventana."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:195
msgid ""
"This will cause that command to split the window vertically instead of "
"horizontally."
msgstr ""
"Esto puede hacer que la ventana se divida verticalmente en lugar de "
"horizontalmente."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:195
msgid "(If the command doesn't split a window, it works unmodified.)"
msgstr "(Si la orden no divide ventanas se ejecuta de modo normal.)"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:202
msgid ""
"Since you can split windows horizontally and vertically as much as you like, "
"you can create almost any layout of windows."
msgstr ""
"Ya que puede dividir ventanas horizontal y verticalmente a voluntad, puede "
"crear casi cualquier estructura."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:202
msgid "Then you can use these commands to move between them:"
msgstr "Una vez las haya creado se puede desplazar por ellas:"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:207
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"CTRL-W h\tmove to the window on the left\n"
"\tCTRL-W j\tmove to the window below\n"
"\tCTRL-W k\tmove to the window above\n"
"\tCTRL-W l\tmove to the window on the right"
msgstr ""
"CTRL-W h        moverse a la ventana de la izquierda\n"
"\tCTRL-W j        moverse a la ventana de abajo\n"
"\tCTRL-W k        moverse a la ventana de arriba\n"
"\tCTRL-W l        moverse a la ventana de la derecha"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:210
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"CTRL-W t\tmove to the TOP window\n"
"\tCTRL-W b\tmove to the BOTTOM window"
msgstr ""
"CTRL-W t        moverse a la ventana superior (TOP)\n"
"\tCTRL-W b        moverse a la ventana inferior (BOTTOM)"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:214
#, no-wrap
msgid "You will notice the same letters as used for moving the cursor."
msgstr ""
"Se habrá dado cuenta de que son las mismas teclas empleadas para mover el\n"
"cursor."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:214
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"And the\n"
"cursor keys can also be used, if you like."
msgstr "También puede usar las teclas de flechas si lo desea."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:214
#, no-wrap
msgid "More commands to move to other windows: |Q_wi|."
msgstr "Más órdenes para moverse a otras ventanas: |Q_wi|."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:217
#, no-wrap
msgid "*08.5*\tMoving windows"
msgstr "*08.5*\tMover ventanas"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:221
msgid "You have split a few windows, but now they are in the wrong place."
msgstr ""
"Imagine que ha creado unas cuantas ventanas, pero están en el lugar "
"equivocado."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:221
msgid "Then you need a command to move the window somewhere else."
msgstr "Necesitará una orden para mover las ventanas a otro lugar."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:221
msgid "For example, you have three windows like this:"
msgstr "Por ejemplo, tiene tres ventanas como estas:"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:236
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"+----------------------------------+\n"
"\t|/* file two.c */\t\t   |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t|two.c=============================|\n"
"\t|/* file three.c */\t\t   |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t|three.c===========================|\n"
"\t|/* file one.c */\t\t   |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t|one.c=============================|\n"
"\t|\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t+----------------------------------+"
msgstr ""
"+----------------------------------+\n"
"\t|/* archivo dos.c */\t\t   |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t|dos.c=============================|\n"
"\t|/* archivo tres.c */\t\t   |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t|tres.c============================|\n"
"\t|/* archivo uno.c */\t\t   |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t|uno.c=============================|\n"
"\t|\t\t\t\t   |\n"
"\t+----------------------------------+"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:239
msgid "Clearly the last one should be at the top."
msgstr "Obviamente la última ventana debería estar en la parte superior."

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:239
msgid "Go to that window (using CTRL-W w)  and the type this command: >"
msgstr ""
"Vaya a esa ventana (usando CTRL-W w) y luego teclee la siguiente orden: >"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:241
#, no-wrap
msgid "CTRL-W K"
msgstr "CTRL-W K"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:258
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"+-------------------------------------------+\n"
"\t|/* two.c */  |/* three.c */  |/* one.c */  |\n"
"\t|~\t      |~\t      |~\t    |\n"
"\t|~\t      |~\t      |~\t    |\n"
"\t|~\t      |~\t      |~\t    |\n"
"\t|~\t      |~\t      |~\t    |\n"
"\t|~\t      |~\t      |~\t    |\n"
"\t|two.c=========three.c=========one.c========|\n"
"\t|\t\t\t\t\t    |\n"
"\t+-------------------------------------------+"
msgstr ""
"+-------------------------------------------+\n"
"\t|/* dos.c */  |/*  tres.c */  |/* uno.c */  |\n"
"\t|~\t      |~\t      |~\t    |\n"
"\t|~\t      |~\t      |~\t    |\n"
"\t|~\t      |~\t      |~\t    |\n"
"\t|~\t      |~\t      |~\t    |\n"
"\t|~\t      |~\t      |~\t    |\n"
"\t|dos.c==========tres.c=========uno.c========|\n"
"\t|\t\t\t\t\t    |\n"
"\t+-------------------------------------------+"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_08.txt:271
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"+-------------------------------------------+\n"
"\t|/* three.c */\t\t\t\t    |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t\t    |\n"
"\t|~\t\t\t\t\t    |\n"
